==English==

===Pronunciation===
flăt, /flæt/, /<tt>fl{t</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-flat.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æt|-æt]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|flatter|flattest}}

# Having no variations in [[altitude]].
#:''The land around here is '''flat'''.''
# {{italbrac|of a tire}} Deflated, especially because of a [[puncture]].
# {{italbrac|music|voice}} Without variations in pitch.
# {{italbrac|music|note}} Lowered by one semitone.
# {{music}} {{italbrac|note|voice}} Lower in pitch than it should be.
# Of a [[carbonated]] drink, with all or most of its [[carbon dioxide]] having come out of [[solution]] so that the drink no longer [[fizz]]es or contains any [[bubble]]s.
# Uninteresting.
#:''The party was a bit '''flat'''.''
# {{cattag|wine}} Lacking [[acidity]] without being [[sweet]].

====Synonyms====
*(''having no variations in altitude''): [[even]], [[planar]], [[plane]], [[smooth]], [[uniform]]
*(''deflated''): [[deflate]]d
*(''without variations in pitch''): [[monotone]]
*(''uninteresting''): [[boring]], [[dull]], [[uninteresting]]
*(''of wine: lacking acidity''): [[flabby]]

====Antonyms====
*(''having no variations in altitude''): [[bumpy]], [[cratered]], [[hilly]] (''of terrain''), [[rough]] (''of a surface''), [[wrinkled]] (''of a surface'')
*(''music: lowered by one semitone''): [[sharp]] 
*(''music: lower in pitch than it should be''): [[sharp]]

